## STEP 4 — Deploy to Google Cloud Run

### 4.1 Install Google Cloud CLI
```bash
# macOS
brew install --cask google-cloud-sdk

# Linux
curl https://sdk.cloud.google.com | bash
exec -l $SHELL

# Windows: download installer from https://cloud.google.com/sdk/install
```

### 4.2 Login & Set Project
```bash
gcloud auth login
gcloud projects create whatsapp-chatbot-proj --name="WhatsApp Chatbot"
gcloud config set project whatsapp-chatbot-proj

# Enable billing at: https://console.cloud.google.com/billing
# (Cloud Run free tier: 2M requests/month — sufficient for most bots)

# Enable required APIs
gcloud services enable run.googleapis.com
gcloud services enable cloudbuild.googleapis.com
```

### 4.3 Deploy
```bash
# From inside the whatsapp-chatbot/ folder:
gcloud run deploy whatsapp-chatbot \
  --source . \
  --platform managed \
  --region asia-south1 \
  --allow-unauthenticated \
  --set-env-vars "WHATSAPP_TOKEN=YOUR_TOKEN,\
WHATSAPP_PHONE_ID=YOUR_PHONE_ID,\
APP_SECRET=YOUR_APP_SECRET,\
VERIFY_TOKEN=mybot_verify_2024,\
OPENAI_API_KEY=YOUR_OPENAI_KEY,\
SUPABASE_URL=YOUR_SUPABASE_URL,\
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=YOUR_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY"
```

> 💡 **Alternatively**, store secrets in Google Secret Manager for better security (recommended for production).

### 4.4 Get Your Public URL
After deploy completes, you'll see:
```
Service URL: https://whatsapp-chatbot-xxxxxxxxxx-uc.a.run.app
```
**Copy this URL** — you'll need it in Step 5.

Test it:
```bash
curl https://your-url.a.run.app/health
```

---

## STEP 5 — Connect Meta Webhook

1. Go to **https://developers.facebook.com** → Your App → **WhatsApp → Configuration**
2. Under **Webhook**, click **Edit**
3. Set:
   - **Callback URL**: `https://your-cloud-run-url.a.run.app/webhook`
   - **Verify token**: same value as `VERIFY_TOKEN` in your `.env`
4. Click **Verify and Save**
   - Meta will call your `/webhook` GET endpoint — your app will respond and verification passes ✅
5. Under **Webhook fields**, click **Manage** and subscribe to **messages**

---

## STEP 6 — Test End-to-End

1. In Meta Dashboard → **WhatsApp → API Setup**, find your test number
2. Add your personal WhatsApp number as a test recipient
3. Send a WhatsApp message to your test number
4. You should get an AI reply within seconds! 🎉

### Check Supabase Data
- Supabase Dashboard → **Table Editor → messages**
- You'll see all conversations stored with phone numbers, roles, and timestamps
- Use **Table Editor → contact_summary** view for a nice overview

